# gitkit

Read-only repo-analysis toolkit â€” point luxe at an existing git repo and get a
packaged markdown report. Three kinds: `gitsummary` (project / deps / health /
use-risk verdict), `gitreview` (serious bug & security findings), `gitrefactor`
(ordered structural refactor plan). Additive front-end; reuses `run_single`,
the read-only tool surface, and the prompt registry's existing overlays.

Exposed two ways: `luxe gitsummary|gitreview|gitrefactor <repo>` (+ aliases
git-summary/gsum, git-review/grev, git-refactor/gref) over an arbitrary local
path or git URL; and `/gitsummary|/gitreview|/gitrefactor` in `luxe chat` over
the session's pinned repo.

## Must
- Be READ-ONLY: run through `make_read_only_role` (mcp/server.py); never write or
  edit the target repo. No `/write` required.
- Be SINGLE-PASS: exactly ONE `run_single` call per report. No autonomous repair
  loop, no follow-up agent runs, no goal-runner â€” a deterministic cost envelope.
  (Do not "optimize" this into a mini-maintain workflow.)
- Inject git-health + GitHub metadata ONLY as data via `run_single`'s
  `extra_context`, tagged `<repo_health>` / `<github_metadata>`. The block is
  pure data and must carry no instruction-like text.
- Gather GitHub data out-of-band through the `gh` CLI in `health.py`, never by
  adding `gh` to the shared bash allowlist (tools/shell.py `_ALLOWLIST` is the
  benchmark tool surface). All `gh` calls go through one helper that degrades
  gracefully (gh missing / unauthenticated / non-GitHub remote / timeout / empty
  repo) to a single-line placeholder; the report still renders from local git.
- Map each kind to an EXISTING task_type/overlay (gitsummaryâ†’summarize,
  gitreviewâ†’review, gitrefactorâ†’review). The per-kind directive rides in the
  `goal` via a `*_HINT` constant from `agents/prompts.py` â€” no new task types,
  no prompt-registry churn.
- Save reports to `~/.luxe/reports/<repo_hash>/<kind>-<ts>-<rand>.md` (always
  `mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)`; `repo_hash` from memory/project.py).
- CLI targets an arbitrary repo; REPL analyzes ONLY `session.repo_path` (reusing
  the session's resident indices) and warns if HEAD moved since indices built.

## Must not
- Write/edit the target repo, or require write mode.
- Add tools to the shared bash allowlist, or mutate `run_single`/`run_agent`
  signatures.
- Read `~/.claude/` or the repo-root `CLAUDE.md`.
- Run more than one agent pass per report (no repair/iteration loop).

## Owns
- src/luxe/gitkit/**

## Forbids
- Prompt/directive strings here â€” they live in `agents/prompts.py`
  (`GIT_SUMMARY_HINT` / `GIT_REVIEW_HINT` / `GIT_REFACTOR_HINT`).
